{
  "stem": "8252.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My feeling was, I want to get to France where we already heard around October maybe, November, that the Polish army is being reconstructed in France and that there will be a Polish divisions of the French army fighting at the front.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, that's my-- that's my way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm going there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had that and a friend of mine also got his passport extended and his visa to Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Which is what is very significant here to the story, is that the visa through Germany expired many days before the extension of the passport expired.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They both had expiration dates.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother had this, and my mother started that she has to go to America and she has to go to America for a very simple reason.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not to save her life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Her daughter was pregnant, and what mother would stay in Poland under the Germans when her daughter is in very good comfort in America, but is pregnant?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So, of course, she has to go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And as I mentioned, that my mother was an amputee and had an artificial leg.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one day I drove her to the train, and I found out that Jews could not get into passenger cars, that they had to go into freight cars.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said to my mother, look, other people have no papers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You have papers but you have-- this is not for you.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You cannot go this way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She has to go.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Anyhow, the next day I took two, two workers from my factory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They placed my mother in a-- in a freight car and went with her all the way to the former Polish-German border.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
